<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fair-adj">fair <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /feə(r)/    美 /fer/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>公平的；公正的；合理的</strong></h4>
<p>反 unfair </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a fair price
合理的价格</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It's not fair</strong>!
这不公平！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I think <strong>it is fair to say that</strong> Cannes is the most famous and exciting festival.
戛纳电影节是最负盛名和最激动人心的电影节，我认为这样说是公平的。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>相当大的；相当多的</strong></h4>
<p>quite good, large, etc.：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a fair amount of money
许多钱</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>There's a fair chance that</strong> we might win this time.
这次我们获胜的可能性很大。/这次我们很有可能获胜。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(肤色) 白皙的；(头发) 浅色的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 dark </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is a tall girl with fair hair.
她身材高挑，有一头浅发。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-fine">4.★ <strong>晴朗的(fine)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It will be fair tomorrow.
明天会是个好天。</p></div></div>